Data model for the stroke tree consumed by `viz/index.html`'s visualization UI; `build.rs` is the assembly pass that populates a `Tree`, and this file defines only the shapes and a couple of key-derivation helpers used during that assembly.

`Tree` holds `categories` (root-level groupings, file order), `node_order` (all node keys in first-seen/first-created order, for deterministic output), and `nodes` (a `HashMap<String, Node>` keyed by identity string). `Node` represents either a real stroke or a synthetic "axis" choice node standing in for several `@count`/`@fuse` alternatives that were bucketed together — presence of `Node.axis: Option<Axis>` distinguishes the two cases; when set, `children` holds a single synthetic axis key instead of real stroke children. A `Node` can carry both `multi_line` and `one_liner` rendered preview strings simultaneously (a stroke can have both variants), plus an optional `one_liner_root` — the `U`-augmented first `/`-segment that actually differs in the one-liner form (see `lineflag.rs` for what that augmentation means) — which is only ever populated alongside `one_liner`.

The key correctness logic lives in `group_key` and `strip_u`: a one-liner variant and its multi-line sibling must collapse into the *same* node, so `group_key` strips the injected `U` marker from the first stroke segment's key set before using the joined stroke as the identity key. This can't be done by naive string splicing because removing a key from a stroke's mid bank can change hyphen placement on re-render (depends on which keys remain present) — so `strip_u` reparses the segment via `parse_stroke`, removes `U` from the `KeySet.mid`, and re-renders via `render_stroke` to get the canonical string. `group_key` only touches the first `/`-segment (splits on the first `/`) since the one-liner marker only ever appears there.

`position(key, category_label) -> String` computes a leaf's parent-bucket identity for tree-building: for a stroke with a `/`-separated prefix, returns everything before the last `/`; for a root-level stroke (no `/`), returns a synthetic `cat:{category_label}` string so that root-level bucketing reuses the same grouping mechanism as descendant bucketing (i.e., callers building the tree don't need a separate special case for roots).

Depends on `steno::{KeySet, TypedEntry, parse_stroke, render_stroke}` (the core stroke parser/renderer) and `crate::axis::Axis`, whose bucketing rule for what counts as one axis is defined in `axis.rs`, not here.